race.comment: GLOWING RAPIDS (3) chasing the hat-trick today after running his rivals into the ground as fav when saluting over 1100m at Narromine in BM66 class. Up sharply in weight but will take holding out. MISSILE DEFENCE (6) failed to backup his good second at Orange when a tiring tenth over 1000m at Canberra. Deserves another chance in this weaker contest. CROOK (4) defeated inferior opposition as fav from the wide gate when racing on the speed over 1000m at Orange. Tricky map today but looks to have plenty of upside. SHADDAP (1) talented gelding resuming. Total forgive from the outside gate when eleventh at this track in the Panorama over 1300m last September. Fitted with the one trial placing over 1000m and sure to be thereabouts .
